genresAdvancedInfo.name: mexican thrash metal
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Mexican thrash metal is a subgenre of heavy metal that emerged in Mexico in the 1980s. It is characterized by its fast and aggressive sound, with distorted guitar riffs, pounding drums, and screamed vocals that convey a sense of anger and rebellion. The lyrics often deal with social and political issues, as well as personal struggles.
